5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 752, L.D. 1147, “An Act Regarding the
10 Required State of Mind Relating to the Threatening Display or Carrying of a Concealed
11 Weapon”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act Regarding the Required State of Mind Relating to the Threatening Display
14 of a Weapon'
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.) by
16 striking out the following: ", intentionally or knowingly"
17 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1 in paragraph A in the first line (page 1, line
18 6 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "in a" and inserting the following: 'in a an
19 intentionally or knowingly'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, updates the
2244 intentionally or knowingly requirement of the prohibition on a threatening display of or the
2255 carrying of a concealed weapon to only apply to the threatening display of a weapon. The
2266 amendment also changes the title of the bill.
